      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs(hooks): document subagent_ended hook event fields (fixes #95186)",
        "body": "### Summary\n\n- **Problem**: The `subagent_ended` plugin hook is listed in the hooks reference alongside `subagent_spawned`, but its event fields (`targetSessionKey`, `targetKind`, `reason`, `sendFarewell`, `accountId`, `runId`, `endedAt`, `outcome`, `error`) are not documented. Plugin authors must read the TypeScript type definition to understand what fields are available.\n- **Root Cause**: When the `subagent_ended` hook was added to the type system (`PluginHookSubagentEndedEvent` in `hook-types.ts`), the corresponding documentation in `docs/plugins/hooks.md` was not updated.\n- **Fix**: Add field-level documentation for `subagent_ended` in the hooks reference, matching the style used for other hooks.\n- **What changed**:\n  - `docs/plugins/hooks.md` — added 9-field documentation for `subagent_ended` hook event\n\n### Change Type\n\n- [x] Documentation\n\n### Scope\n\n- [x] docs / plugin hooks reference\n\n### Linked Issue/PR\n\nFixes #95186",
